  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "The 13.1 and 26.2 stickers are commonly used by runners to represent their completion of half-marathons and marathons, respectively. The numbers refer to the distances in miles that are covered in these races. A half-marathon is 13.1 miles long, while a full marathon is 26.2 miles. These stickers are often seen on cars, water bottles, or personal items as a way for runners to proudly display their achievements. They serve as a badge of honor and can be a conversation starter among fellow runners and enthusiasts.",
